@items.name: person_id
@items.description: A unique identifier for each person.

@items.description: A foreign key that refers to an identifier in the CONCEPT table for the unique gender of the person.

@items.name: year_of_birth
@items.description: The year of birth of the person. For data sources with date of birth, the year is extracted. For data sources where the year of birth is not available, the approximate year of birth is derived based on any age group categorization available.

@items.description: The month of birth of the person. For data sources that provide the precise date of birth, the month is extracted and stored in this field.

@items.description: The day of the month of birth of the person. For data sources that provide the precise date of birth, the day is extracted and stored in this field.

@items.name: death_datetime
@items.description: The date and time of death of the person.

@items.description: A foreign key that refers to the standard concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies for the ethnicity of the person.

@items.name: location_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the place of residency for the person in the location table, where the detailed address information is stored.

@items.name: provider_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the primary care provider the person is seeing in the provider table.

@items.name: care_site_id

@items.description: An (encrypted) key derived from the person identifier in the source data. This is necessary when a use case requires a link back to the person data at the source dataset.

@items.name: race_source_value
@items.description: The source code for the race of the person as it appears in the source data. The person race is mapped to a standard race concept in the Standardized Vocabularies and the original value is stored here for reference.

@items.name: race_source_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the race concept that refers to the code used in the source.

@items.name: ethnicity_source_value

@items.name: unit_concept_id

@items.name: dose_value
@items.description: The numeric value of the dose.

@items.name: dose_era_start_datetime
@items.description: The start date for the drug era constructed from the individual instances of drug exposures. It is the start date of the very first chronologically recorded instance of utilization of a drug.

@items.name: dose_era_end_datetime
@items.description: The end date for the drug era constructed from the individual instance of drug exposures. It is the end date of the final continuously recorded instance of utilization of a drug.

@items.name: drug_era_id
@items.description: A unique identifier for each Drug Era.

@items.name: person_id
@items.description: A foreign key identifier to the Person who is subjected to the Drug during the fDrug Era. The demographic details of that Person are stored in the PERSON table.

@items.name: drug_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key that refers to a Standard Concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies for the Ingredient Concept.

@items.name: drug_era_start_datetime
@items.description: The start date for the Drug Era constructed from the individual instances of Drug Exposures. It is the start date of the very first chronologically recorded instance of conutilization of a Drug.

@items.name: drug_era_end_datetime
@items.description: The end date for the drug era constructed from the individual instance of drug exposures. It is the end date of the final continuously recorded instance of utilization of a drug.

@items.name: drug_exposure_count
@items.description: The number of individual Drug Exposure occurrences used to construct the Drug Era.

@items.name: gap_days
@items.description: The number of days that are not covered by DRUG_EXPOSURE records that were used to make up the era record.

@items.name: cost_id
@items.description: A unique identifier for each COST record.

@items.name: person_id
@items.description: A unique identifier for each PERSON.

@items.name: cost_event_id
@items.description: A foreign key identifier to the event (e.g. Measurement, Procedure, Visit, Drug Exposure, etc) record for which cost data are recorded.

@items.name: cost_event_field_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key identifier to a concept in the CONCEPT table representing the identity of the field represented by COST_EVENT_ID

@items.name: cost_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key that refers to a Standard Cost Concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies belonging to the 'Cost' vocabulary.

@items.name: cost_type_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key identifier to a concept in the CONCEPT table for the provenance or the source of the COST data and belonging to the 'Cost Type' vocabulary

@items.conceptName: Amount charged to the patient or the payer by the provider, list price
Amount paid by the patient or reimbursed by the payer

@items.name: cost_source_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a Cost Concept that refers to the code used in the source.

@items.name: cost_source_value
@items.description: The source value for the cost as it appears in the source data

@items.name: currency_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key identifier to the concept representing the 3-letter code used to delineate international currencies, such as USD for US Dollar. These belong to the 'Currency' vocabulary

@items.name: cost
@items.description: The actual financial cost amount

@items.name: incurred_date
@items.description: The first date of service of the clinical event corresponding to the cost as in table capturing the information (e.g. date of visit, date of procedure, date of condition, date of drug etc).

@items.name: billed_date
@items.description: The date a bill was generated for a service or encounter

@items.name: paid_date
@items.description: The date payment was received for a service or encounter

@items.name: revenue_code_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key referring to a Standard Concept ID in the Standardized Vocabularies for Revenue codes belonging to the 'Revenue Code' vocabulary.

@items.name: drg_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key referring to a Standard Concept ID in the Standardized Vocabularies for DRG codes belonging to the 'DRG' vocabulary.

@items.name: revenue_code_source_value
@items.description: The source value for the Revenue code as it appears in the source data, stored here for reference.

@items.name: drg_source_value
@items.description: The source value for the 3-digit DRG source code as it appears in the source data, stored here for reference.

@items.name: payer_plan_period_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the PAYER_PLAN_PERIOD table, where the details of the Payer, Plan and Family are stored. Record the payer_plan_id that relates to the payer who contributed to the paid_by_payer field.

@items.name: payer_plan_period_id
@items.description: A identifier for each unique combination of payer, sponsor, plan, family code and time span.

@items.name: person_id
@items.description: A foreign key identifier to the Person covered by the payer. The demographic details of that Person are stored in the PERSON table.

@items.name: contract_person_id
@items.description: A foreign key identifier to the person_id in person table, for the person who is the primary subscriber/contract owner for the record in the payer_plan_period table. Maybe the same person or different person, depending on who is the primary subscriber/contract owner.

@items.name: payer_plan_period_start_date
@items.description: The start date of the payer plan period.

@items.name: payer_plan_period_end_date
@items.description: The end date of the payer plan period.

@items.name: payer_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key that refers to a Standard Payer concept identifiers in the Standardized Vocabularies

@items.name: payer_source_value
@items.description: The source code for the payer as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: payer_source_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a payer concept that refers to the code used in the source.

@items.name: plan_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key that refers to a Standard plan that represents the health benefit plan in the Standardized Vocabularies

@items.name: plan_source_value
@items.description: The source code for the Person's health benefit plan as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: plan_source_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a plan concept that refers to the code used in the source.

@items.name: contract_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a standard concept representing the reason justifying the contract between person_id and contract_person_id.

@items.name: contract_source_value
@items.description: The source code representing the reason justifying the contract. Usually it is family relationship like a spouse, domestic partner, child etc.

@items.name: contract_source_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a concept that refers to the code used in the source as the reason justifying the contract.

@items.name: sponsor_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key that refers to a Standard plan that represents the sponsor in the Standardized Vocabularies

@items.name: sponsor_source_value
@items.description: The source code for the Person's sponsor of the health plan as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: sponsor_source_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a sponsor concept that refers to the code used in the source.

@items.name: family_source_value
@items.description: The source code for the Person's family as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: stop_reason_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key that refers to a Standard termination reason that represents the reason for the termination in the Standardized Vocabularies.

@items.name: stop_reason_source_value
@items.description: The reason for stop-coverage of the record.

@items.name: stop_reason_source_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a stop-coverage concept that refers to the code used in the source.

@items.name: care_site_id
@items.description: A unique identifier for each Care Site.

@items.name: care_site_name
@items.description: The verbatim description or name of the Care Site as in data source

@items.name: place_of_service_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key that refers to a Place of Service Concept ID in the Standardized Vocabularies.

@items.name: location_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the geographic Location in the LOCATION table, where the detailed address information is stored.

@items.name: care_site_source_value
@items.description: The identifier for the Care Site in the source data, stored here for reference.

@items.name: place_of_service_source_value
@items.description: The source code for the Place of Service as it appears in the source data, stored here for reference.

@items.name: location_id
@items.description: A unique identifier for each geographic location.

@items.name: address_1
@items.description: The address field 1, typically used for the street address, as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: address_2
@items.description: The address field 2, typically used for additional detail such as buildings, suites, floors, as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: city
@items.description: The city field as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: state
@items.description: The state field as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: zip
@items.description: The zip or postal code.

@items.name: county
@items.description: The county.

@items.name: country
@items.description: The country

@items.name: location_source_value
@items.description: The verbatim information that is used to uniquely identify the location as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: latitude
@items.description: The geocoded latitude

@items.name: longitude
@items.description: The geocoded longitude

@items.name: provider_id
@items.description: A unique identifier for each Provider.

@items.name: provider_name
@items.description: A description of the Provider.

@items.name: npi
@items.description: The National Provider Identifier (NPI) of the provider.

@items.name: dea
@items.description: The Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA) number of the provider.

@items.name: specialty_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a Standard Specialty Concept ID in the Standardized Vocabularies.

@items.name: care_site_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the main Care Site where the provider is practicing.

@items.name: year_of_birth
@items.description: The year of birth of the Provider.

@items.name: gender_concept_id
@items.description: The gender of the Provider.

@items.name: provider_source_value
@items.description: The identifier used for the Provider in the source data, stored here for reference.

@items.name: specialty_source_value
@items.description: The source code for the Provider specialty as it appears in the source data, stored here for reference.

@items.name: specialty_source_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a Concept that refers to the code used in the source.

@items.name: gender_source_value
@items.description: The gender code for the Provider as it appears in the source data, stored here for reference.

@items.name: gender_source_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a Concept that refers to the code used in the source.

@items.name: cdm_source_name
@items.description: The full name of the source

@items.name: cdm_source_abbreviation
@items.description: An abbreviation of the name

@items.name: cdm_holder
@items.description: The name of the organization responsible for the development of the CDM instance

@items.name: source_description
@items.description: A description of the source data origin and purpose for collection. The description may contain a summary of the period of time that is expected to be covered by this dataset.

@items.name: source_documentation_reference
@items.description: URL or other external reference to location of source documentation

@items.name: cdm_etl_reference
@items.description: URL or other external reference to location of ETL specification documentation and ETL source code

@items.name: source_release_date
@items.description: The date for which the source data are most current, such as the last day of data capture

@items.name: cdm_release_date
@items.description: The date when the CDM was instantiated

@items.name: cdm_version
@items.description: The version of CDM used

@items.name: vocabulary_version
@items.description: The version of the vocabulary used

@items.name: metadata_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key that refers to a Standard Metadata Concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies.

@items.name: metadata_type_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key that refers to a Standard Type Concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies.

@items.name: name
@items.description: The name of the Concept stored in metadata_concept_id or a description of the data being stored.

@items.name: value_as_string
@items.description: The metadata value stored as a string.

@items.name: value_as_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a metadata value stored as a Concept ID.

@items.name: metadata date
@items.description: The date associated with the metadata

@items.name: metadata_datetime
@items.description: The date and time associated with the metadata

@items.name: cohort_definition_id
@items.description: A unique identifier for each Cohort.

@items.name: cohort_definition_name
@items.description: A short description of the Cohort.

@items.name: cohort_definition_description
@items.description: A complete description of the Cohort definition

@items.name: definition_type_concept_id
@items.description: Type defining what kind of Cohort Definition the record represents and how the syntax may be executed

@items.name: cohort_definition_syntax
@items.description: Syntax or code to operationalize the Cohort definition

@items.name: subject_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the Concept to which defines the domain of subjects that are members of the cohort (e.g., Person, Provider, Visit).

@items.name: cohort_initiation_date
@items.description: A date to indicate when the Cohort was initiated in the COHORT table

@items.name: survey_conduct_id
@items.description: Unique identifier for each completed survey.

@items.name: person_id
@items.description: A foreign key identifier to the Person in the PERSON table about whom the survey was completed.

@items.name: survey_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the predefined Concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies reflecting the name and identity of the survey.

@items.name: survey_start_date
@items.description: Date on which the survey was started.

@items.name: survey_start_datetime
@items.description: Date and time the survey was started.

@items.name: survey_end_date
@items.description: Date on which the survey was completed.

@items.name: survey_end_datetime
@items.description: Date and time the survey was completed.

@items.name: provider_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the provider in the provider table who was associated with the survey completion.

@items.name: assisted_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the predefined Concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies indicating whether the survey was completed with assistance.

@items.name: respondent_type_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the predefined Concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies reflecting the respondent type. Example: Research Associate, Patient.

@items.name: timing_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the predefined Concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies that refers to a certain timing. Example: 3 month follow-up, 6 month follow-up.

@items.name: collection_method_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the predefined Concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies reflecting the data collection method (e.g. Paper, Telephone, Electronic Questionnaire).

@items.name: assisted_source_value
@items.description: Source value representing whether patient required assistance to complete the survey. Example: "Completed without assistance", "Completed with assistance".

@items.name: respondent_type_source_value
@items.description: Source code representing role of person who completed the survey.

@items.name: timing_source_value
@items.description: Text string representing the timing of the survey. Example: Baseline, 6-month follow-up.

@items.name: collection_method_source_value
@items.description: The collection method as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: survey_source_value
@items.description: The survey name/title as it appears in the source data.

@items.name: survey_source_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to a predefined Concept that refers to the code for the survey name/title used in the source.

@items.name: survey_source_identifier
@items.description: Unique identifier for each completed survey in source system.

@items.name: validated_survey_concept_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the predefined Concept identifier in the Standardized Vocabularies reflecting the validation status of the survey.

@items.name: validated_survey_source_value
@items.description: Source value representing the validation status of the survey.

@items.name: survey_version_number
@items.description: Version number of the questionnaire or survey used.

@items.name: visit_occurrence_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the VISIT_OCCURRENCE table during which the survey was completed

@items.name: response_visit_occurrence_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the visit in the VISIT_OCCURRENCE table during which treatment was carried out that relates to this survey.

@items.name: location_id
@items.description: A foreign key to the location table.

@items.name: relationship_type_concept_id
@items.description: The type of relationship between location and entity.

@items.name: domain_id
@items.description: The domain of the entity that is related to the location. Either PERSON, PROVIDER, or CARE_SITE.

@items.name: entity_id
@items.description: The unique identifier for the entity. References either person_id, provider_id, or care_site_id, depending on domain_id.

@items.name: start_date
@items.description: The date the relationship started.

@items.name: end_date
@items.description: The date the relationship ended.
